  "text": "Many approaches attack the problem from a different angle; they try to improve energy efficiency of the data center by taking into account the specific nature of cluster workload. In [CITATION_1] ) the authors found out that in thousands-server-size data centers there is 7% to 16% gap between achieved peak power and theoretical peak power reported by a manufacturer. They suggest to host additional servers under the existing power budget and to mix different workloads to get smoother combined workload. In [CITATION_2] ) the authors propose to exploit data center uninterrupted power supplies (UPSs) during the increased workload period to shave such power peaks. The UPSs are then loaded during the lower activity workload. The authors present an algorithm which investigates the whole day workload and draw electricity from UPSs during the highest activity.",
